OL,3,C'Everybody's scared': Fears over
OL,4,Cbenefit cuts as Starmer defends
OL,5,Cwelfare reforms
OL,7,FSir Keir Starmer said: "The welfare
OL,8,Fsystem as it's set up, it can't be
OL,9,Fdefended on economic terms or moral
OL,10,Fterms.
OL,12,F"Economically, the cost is going
OL,13,Fthrough the roof. So if we don't do
OL,14,Fanything, the cost of welfare is going
OL,15,Fto go to #70 billion per year. That's
OL,16,Fa third of the cost of the NHS.
OL,18,F"That's more than the Home Office and
OL,19,Four prisons combined. So we're making
OL,20,Fchoices here."
