OL,3,C'Everybody's scared': Fears over
OL,4,Cbenefit cuts as Starmer defends
OL,5,Cwelfare reforms
OL,7,FMeanwhile, the Labour MP for
OL,8,FMiddlesbrough South and East
OL,9,FCleveland, Luke Myer, agreed that
OL,10,Freforming the system is necessary.
OL,12,FHe said: "We should be really clear
OL,13,Fhere, that the welfare system in this
OL,14,Fcountry is totally broken, and it's
OL,15,Ffailing people every single day.
OL,17,F"The number of young people who are
OL,18,Fnot in education, employment or
OL,19,Ftraining is approaching a million
OL,20,Fpeople, it's a lost generation and it
OL,21,Fneeds to change."
